detail.title: OIP4 -Implementing Replicated Security for a More Robust and Expansive Ecosystem
detail.description: This upgrade includes addition of the Replicated Security Provider module, removal of the gravity module and an upgrade to Cosmos-SDK v0.45.16 with RS and custom patches. An updated gravity module will be added later to its own consumer chain. Further details and discussion regarding OIP 4 may be found here:  https://forum.onomy.io/t/oip-4-implementing-replicated-security-for-a-more-robust-and-expansive-ecosystem

detail.title: OIP-6 Update 2: Discontinue Indiscriminate Delegation of DAO Treasury
detail.description: This proposal includes a follow up to the software upgrade that discontinued the delegation of NOM in the DAO Treasury to validators. It further corrects the staking APR by only accounting for bonded Active Supply, abstracting the DAO Treasury's tokens. Further details and discussion regarding OIP 6 may be found here:  https://forum.onomy.io/t/oip-6-discontinue-validator-rewards-from-dao-delegation

detail.title: OIP-6: Discontinue Indiscriminate Delegation of DAO Treasury
detail.description: This proposal includes a software upgrade that discontinues the indiscriminate delegation of NOM in the DAO Treasury to validators, paving way to a value add-focused delegation policy. The DAO Treasury will continue to be inflated at the same APR as other NOM delegations.  Further details and discussion regarding OIP 6 may be found here:  https://forum.onomy.io/t/oip-6-discontinue-validator-rewards-from-dao-delegation

detail.title: upgrade to v1.0.3
detail.description:
OIP-5 Chain Upgrade: Lower Staking Rewards to Cosmos SDK Default Range (7-20%) 
This proposal aims to remediate current high inflationary staking reward rate of 114% by lowering the staking reward rate to the Cosmos SDK default range of 7-20%. By adjusting the staking rewards earlier, Onomy may create a more sustainable and stable ecosystem that benefits all stakeholders in the long term.
Please visit the forum OIP 5 post for more information and discussion regarding this proposed chain upgrade: https://forum.onomy.io/t/oip-5-lower-staking-rewards-to-cosmos-sdk-default-range-7-20

detail.title: OIP-6 Chain Upgrade: Discontinue indiscriminate DAO Treasury Delegation to Validators.
detail.description: DAO Treasury Delegation should be more purpose-driven to reward good-acting validators. By discontinuing indiscriminate DAO delegation staking rewards to validators, rewards will be more balanced creating a more sustainable, secure, and decentralized ecosystem that benefits all stakeholders. Delegations must instead be earned organically by reliable validators making contributions to Onomy’s Ecosystem. Please visit the forum OIP-6 post for more information and discussion regarding this proposed chain upgrade: https://forum.onomy.io/t/oip-6-discontinue-validator-rewards-from-dao-delegation/283

detail.title: Parameter change: Slashing Fraction - Downtime
detail.description: The goal of this proposal is to decrease the downtime slashing fraction parameter from 1% to 0.05%. We believe this threshold should be lowered, specifically because there is an additional sidecar that needs to be run in parallel to the standard validation binary on Onomy. As experience tells us on other networks such as Injective or Band, these sidecars tend to behave unstable at times. At present, the slashing parameter is also unusually strict as compared to other large Cosmos networks. We believe a reduction by 20x would be reasonable given these observations and the early stage of the network.

detail.title: Bonding Curve Proceeds
detail.description:
Dear Nomads,


Pendulum is writing to request approval from the DAO to continue receiving revenue generated from the Bonding Curve, which has been deployed on the Ethereum mainnet and launched in tandem with Mainnet Prior to the mainnet launch, Pendulum Labs developed the code for the Bonding Curve and deployed it tandem with the mainnet launch.  The code has been audited by NCC Group, a reputable cybersecurity firm. After the deployment, the Bonding Curve was approved by the genesis set of validators who recognized the value of the Bonding Curve and its potential to provide liquidity and value to the ecosystem.


While  approval was received from the genesis set of validators, Pendulum Labs recognizes the importance of seeking approval from the wider community through the DAO. We understand that the DAO has the authority to approve or reject our request to continue receiving revenue from the Bonding Curve. 


Now that the Onomy community stands at over 65,000 members in Discord with an incredible community of Nomads that has been formed in all regions of the world (shoutout to Spain, Eastern Europe, Singapore, Indonesia, China, and many more rapidly growing regions) - we respectfully request re-approval from the DAO for Pendulum Labs to continue receiving revenue from the Bonding Curve. We believe that our development of the Bonding Curve warrants our receipt of the funds, which have been and will continue to be used to facilitate ongoing development of other blockchain and cryptoasset products and services outside of Onomy, like Access Wallet, nodes for Cosmos chains, IBC relayers, etc.


The purpose of the Bonding Curve was interwoven into the fabric of Onomy’s design to be decentralized from day one. As you know, contributors to Onomy have gone to great lengths to be decentralized from day 1 and relinquish control at every facet; such as placing the entire treasury on-chain in a wallet fully governed by Onomy’s DAO - removing the keys from any central entity, Foundation, and the founding team. 


We recognize that Onomy is a strong and capable ecosystem that can continue to operate without our involvement. However, we believe that Pendulum Labs can provide additional value to the greater blockchain and cryptoasset ecosystem by contributing to business development efforts alongside others, such as Cosmosatation, Forbole, Citadel One, Strangelove, and more. 


By continuing to receive revenue from the Bonding Curve, Pendulum Labs can remain fully committed to supporting continued research, development and the provision of services to the blockchain and cryptoasset ecosystem as a whole, of which we are proud to be a part.


Thank you for your consideration, 


Pendulum Labs

detail.title: Funding for Pendulum Labs
detail.description:
Dear Nomads,

Pendulum Labs is pleased to present this proposal for funding of 5 million NOM tokens from the Onomy protocol treasury. As a core contributor to the Onomy Protocol, our team at Pendulum Labs is dedicated to furthering the Onomy agenda and mission to converge Forex and DeFi.

Our team has a proven track record of success, contributing to the Arc Bridge Hub, interfaces for Onomy's decentralized products to improve user experience and accessibility for the community, crafting the Discord community restructure and Crew3 tasks, which have been well received by the Nomads.

The funding requested will not only be utilized to maintain Pendulum Labs as a legal entity, allowing us to sign contracts with market makers, liquidity providers, and exchanges, but it will also sustain the operations, allowing us to continue to contribute to the Onomy ecosystem. Furthermore, the funding will be used to expand the validator set and create reward pools for Nomads through Crew3 task rewards and liquidity incentives. Additionally, we plan to use the funding to establish strategic partnerships to further ecosystem growth and adoption of the Onomy protocol.

We understand the importance of responsible and transparent use of protocol funds and assure the Nomads that the requested funding will be used solely for the purpose of advancing Onomy Protocol. We are confident that the results for the Onomy community will include improved user experience, accessibility, community engagement, liquidity provision and ecosystem growth.

We kindly request the Nomads to vote in favor of this proposal!

Thank you for your consideration.

Best regards,
Pendulum Labs

detail.title: Dao Parameteras Change.
detail.description: The goal of this proposal is to increase the pool_rate and max_proposal_rate parameters in order to enable more meaningful proposals at the early stages of the protocol. The pool_rate and max_proposal_rate parameters are used to control number of unstaked NOMs available and the amount of NOMs that can be withdrawn per proposal. At present, these parameters may be set too low to enable meaningful proposals at the early stages of the protocol. This can limit the ability of the DAO to make important decisions and act on important issues. As the protocol matures, these parameters will be gradually reduced to a more appropriate level. This will be done through a series of community discussions and proposals, to ensure that the community is involved in the decision-making process.
